{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Cubemap","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A cubemap is made of 6 textures organized in layers. They are typically used for faking reflections in 3D rendering (see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ReflectionProbe","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"). It can be used to make an object look as if it’s reflecting its surroundings. This usually delivers much better performance than other reflection methods."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This resource is typically used as a uniform in custom shaders. Few core Godot methods make use of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" resources."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create such a texture file yourself, reimport your image files using the Godot Editor import presets."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Godot doesn’t support using cubemaps in a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PanoramaSkyMaterial","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". You can use ","type":"text"},{"text":"this tool","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" to convert a cubemap to an equirectangular sky map."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Six square textures representing the faces of a cube. Commonly used as a skybox."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation